<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="162">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34080" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole vallicola Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole vallicola Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallicola">vallicola</taxonomicName>
, valley dweller, referring to the habitat of the type colony.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="162">
diagnosis A member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33688" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">crassicornis</taxonomicName>
group, similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33688" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">crassicornis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33716" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole diversipilosa Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole diversipilosa Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diversipilosa">diversipilosa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33938" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole porcula Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole porcula Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porcula">porcula</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181655" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tetra Creighton" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tetra Creighton" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetra">tetra</taxonomicName>
, but differing by the following combination of traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="162">Major: pilosity consisting of sparse, very long hairs (some on first gastral tergite are 2X the maximum eye length); head in side view tapered toward occiput; rugoreticulum forms a broad swath from antennal fossa to eye on each side; carinulae along midline of dorsum of head continue to occiput; pronotum sparsely foveolate and feebly shining on sides, smooth and shiny on dorsum; postpetiole from above laterally subangulate.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="162">Minor: petiolar node from side thin, and tapered toward apex; pilosity sparse, as illustrated; dorsum of head (except for frontal triangle and middle section of clypeus), all of mesosoma, and most of waist foveolate and opaque. Measurements (mm) Lectotype major: HW 1.34, HL 1.44, SL 0.80, EL 0.20, PW 0.64. Paralectotype minor: HW 0.64, HL 0.70, SL 0.82, EL 0.14, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="162">color Major: body light reddish brown except for gaster, which is a slightly contrasting medium reddish brown. Minor: concolorous medium reddish brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="162">Range Recorded by Stefan Cover in numerous collections at 1200-1900 m in the following mountain ranges of southeastern Arizona: Chiricahua, Dragoon, Huachuca, Pajarito, Pinal, and Sierra Ancha.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="162">
Biology Stefan Cover (unpublished collection notes) found 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34080" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole vallicola Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole vallicola Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallicola">vallicola</taxonomicName>
to favor creek banks and open woodland with a wide range of species composition, from ponderosa pine to oak, pine-oak-juniper, and oak-mesquite-sumac. Nests were usually under stones in either shade or exposed areas, although occasionally they had been constructed in open soil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
